<ul>
  <li>
    <p>stories for design</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>use and reuse</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

<h2 id="scenarios-1">Scenarios</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Stories for design
    <ul>
      <li>communicate with others</li>
      <li>validate other models</li>
      <li>understand dynamics</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Linearity
    <ul>
      <li>time is linear - our lives are linear</li>
      <li>but don‚Äôt show alternatives</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

<h2 id="scenarios-is-about">Scenarios is about‚Ä¶</h2>

<ul>
  <li>What will users want to do?</li>
  <li>Step-by-step walkthrough
    <ul>
      <li>what can they see (sketches, screen shots)</li>
      <li>what do they do (keyboard, mouse etc.)</li>
      <li>what are they thinking?</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Use and reuse throughout design</li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

<h2 id="scenario--movie-player">Scenario ‚Äì movie player</h2>

<p>Brian would like to see the new film ‚ÄúMoments of Significance‚Äù and wants to invite Alison, but he knows she doesn‚Äôt like ‚Äúarty‚Äù films. He decides to take a look at it to see if she would like it and so connects to one of the movie sharing networks. He uses his work machine as it has a higher bandwidth connection, but feels a bit guilty. He knows he will be getting an illegal copy of the film, but decides it is OK as he is intending to go to the cinema to watch it. After it downloads to his machine he takes out his new personal movie player. He presses the ‚Äòmenu‚Äô button and on the small LCD screen he scrolls using the arrow keys to ‚ÄòBluetooth connect‚Äô and presses the select button. On his computer the movie download program now has an icon showing that it has recognized a compatible device and he drags the icon of the film over the icon for the player. On the player the LCD screen says ‚Äúdownloading now‚Äù, a percent done indicator and small whirling icon. ‚Ä¶ ‚Ä¶ ‚Ä¶</p>

<p><br /></p>

