<h2 id="use-scenarios-to-">Use scenarios to ..</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Communicate with others
    <ul>
      <li>designers, clients, users</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Validate other models
    <ul>
      <li>‚Äòplay‚Äô it against other models</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Express dynamics
    <ul>
      <li>screenshots ‚Äì appearance</li>
      <li>scenario ‚Äì behaviour</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

<h2 id="linearity">Linearity</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Scenarios - one linear path through system</li>
  <li>Pros:
    <ul>
      <li>life and time are linear</li>
      <li>easy to understand (stories and narrative are natural)</li>
      <li>concrete (errors less likely)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Cons:
    <ul>
      <li>no choice, no branches, no special conditions</li>
      <li>miss the unintended</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>So:
    <ul>
      <li>use several scenarios</li>
      <li>use several methods</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

